 <francois-simon.fauteux-chapleau@savoirfairelinux.com>
Date: Tue, 28 Apr 2026 13:06:11 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] qtwebengine: add missing header includes in chromium
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Chromium's build fails on Fedora 44 because of undeclared types, e.g.:

    In file included from ../../../3rdparty/chromium/third_party/perfetto/include/perfetto/ext/tracing/core/trace_packet.h:27,
                     from ../../../3rdparty/chromium/third_party/perfetto/src/tracing/core/trace_packet.cc:17:
    ../../../3rdparty/chromium/third_party/perfetto/include/perfetto/ext/tracing/core/slice.h:47:46: error: ‘uint8_t’ was not declared in this scope
       47 |   static Slice TakeOwnership(std::unique_ptr<uint8_t[]> buf, size_t size) {
          |

This is probably due to standard library header changes in GCC 16.
---
 .../3rdparty/chromium/cc/input/main_thread_scrolling_reason.h    | 1 +
 .../src/3rdparty/chromium/extensions/common/stack_frame.h        | 1 +
 .../src/3rdparty/chromium/net/tools/huffman_trie/trie_entry.h    | 1 +
 .../chromium/third_party/angle/src/image_util/AstcDecompressor.h | 1 +
 .../pdfium/core/fxcodec/jbig2/JBig2_DocumentContext.h            | 1 +
 .../perfetto/include/perfetto/ext/tracing/core/slice.h           | 1 +
 .../3rdparty/chromium/third_party/webrtc/video/stats_counter.h   | 1 +
 .../3rdparty/chromium/third_party/woff2/include/woff2/output.h   | 1 +
 8 files changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/qtwebengine/src/3rdparty/chromium/cc/input/main_thread_scrolling_reason.h b/qtwebengine/src/3rdparty/chromium/cc/input/main_thread_scrolling_reason.h
